TY  - JOUR
AB  - Two-moment decision models are consistent with expected utility maximization only if the choice set or the agent's preferences are restricted. This paper identifies a restriction which is sufficient to ensure this consistency and confirms that it holds in many economic models. The implications for economic analysis are then derived.
